items.description:
Style-LoRA of the artist Owler who was/is especially known for her Korra/Avatar illustrations.

LoRA created via Pixai LoRA onsite-creation. Used 100 Images on high resolution from past patreon rewards.

Weight at 0.5-0.7 seems to be working fine, but it's very dependant on the checkpoint used. All preview images are done with Galena REDUX (v2.0). Highres-Fix recommended!

It may be helpful to add thin lineart in positive promts and/or thick lineart in negative promts to avoid overly thick lineart.

Examples of checkpoints that also seem to work decently. Since the artstyle is cell-shading like 2D-Checkpoints work better.

  • Yotta Mix 5.0

  • SebitaMix v1.0

  • EveryDayArt (EDA) v5.0

  • Orange Galenyx Merge v1.1

This LoRA can especially struggles with hands, keep that in mind when generating.

items.name: Fluffy Style - Add some fuzziness to your images!
items.description:
Get yourself into any kind of hairy situation!

Fluffy clouds, fur coats, fuzzy frills, armpits in need of a shave, this LoRA has it all!

The model tends to add fur coats, mossy environments, large fuzzy fluffs, long fluffy messy hair. Due to the chosen activation keyword, it also adds a lot of furry animals walking on two legs, or animal heads to humans.

Usage

Use the trigger word: "FluffyStyle" along with the LoRA to activate it.

You can usually get the color of fur you want by simply prompting it right after the trigger word.

Example prompt:

FluffyStyle pink snake <lora:FluffyStyle:1>

Recommended weights: 0.7-1.8, most weights are just fine!

Recommended sampler: Euler-a, DPM++ 2M Karras

Recommended steps: 20+

Tips & Tricks

Useful keywords for the prompt:

  • fuzzy

  • furry

  • hairy

  • made out of felt

Like it? Feel free to do the coffee thing:

https://ko-fi.com/mnemic

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/mnemic

items.name: Robocop(Unmasked Alex Murphy)
items.description:
두번째 결과물입니다.

그럴려고 하던 의도가 아닌데... 약간 실사풍보다는 애니메이션 풍에 더 가깝게 결과물이 나와버렸습니다.

로보캅이 Lora가 많은데, 의외로 프랜차이즈 진행 중 종종 나오던 '헬멧을 벗은 로보캅' Lora는 보이지 않아서 이번 기회에 제가 제작하였습니다.

아마 (robocop:1.4), robot, (android:1.4), (chrome metal:1.4), (metal skin:1.4), titanium, (handsome:1.4), shiny skin 등으로 헬멧을 벗은 로보캅 그림을 뽑으실 수 있겠습니다.

(좋은 모델이나 가중치는 잘 모르겠습니다. 모델로서는 fantasticmix가 그나마 괜찮게 뽑아집는데 한번 다양하게 생성해보시기 바랍니다.)

damaged를 추가한다면 잘 적용되는 느낌은 아니더라도 메카바레 느낌도 표현할 수 있겠습니다.

아직 많이 테스트해보진 못했지만, robot girl, (an extremely delicate and beautiful face) 등을 넣으면... 여성형 로보캅도 뽑을 수 있지 않을까요?

더 제작 실력이 좋아지면 더 높은 퀄리티의 2.0 버전도 내고 싶고 다른 로봇 캐릭터들도 Lora를 제작하고 싶습니다.

부디 로보캅을 좋아하시는 분들께 이 Lora가 즐거움이 되었으면 합니다. Lora에다 여러가지 추가해서 더 높은 퀄리티의 머피 그림을 올려주셔요!

ㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡㅡ

Second output of my trials.

It wasn't the intention I had in mind... Instead of a somewhat realistic style, the output ended up closer to an animated style.

Although there are many Robocop Loras, there has not been Lora of 'Robocop without the helmet' that occasionally appeared throughout franchise. So I created it myself.

Perhaps you could generate images of the unmasked Robocop using

prompt: (robocop:1.4), robot, (android:1.4), (chrome metal:1.4), (metal skin:1.4), titanium, (handsome:1.4), shiny skin

(I'm not sure about good models or weights. As a model, the fantastic mix is pulled out pretty well, but you'd better generate a variety of them and find your best option.)

Not that working well, you may be able to add some damaged effect(Mechabare) by adding prompt 'damaged'.

Although I haven't tested it extensively yet,

if you include prompt 'robot girl, (an extremely delicate and beautiful face)', etc...

We may also get a female Robocop?

As my skills in creating improve, I hope to release a higher-quality 2.0 version and create other robot character's Lora.

I sincerely hope that this Lora brings enjoyment to those who love Robocop.

items.name: LasgunXL: Warhammer 40k Lasgun and Cadian SDXL LoRA
items.description:
A LoRA to allow you to incorporate Lasguns from Warhammer 40k into your AI art. It also biases armor pretty heavily towards Cadian/Kasrkin armor unless told otherwise, but it will happily do other outfits.

I recommended weight 0.9-1.0, depending on model. I've been getting reports that on other models, lowering the weight to 0.7-0.6 works better. Experiment!

On mine, RoXL, it works best at 0.9, while on BriXL it works better at 1.0. Somewhere in this rough range should work. I also strongly recommend terms like "rifle" and "holding gun" to help guide SDXL.

The success rate is reasonably good. In my testing about 50% of the lasguns were passable, while maybe 1/8- 1/10 were excellent. For best results, though, slight inpainting is helpful, though the example images are not inpainted.

Finally, training models takes a lot of work, and to train SDXL models I need to pay for time on higher end GPUs, so if you'd like to support me experimenting and making models, feel free to toss me a dollar or two on ko-fi.

items.description:
The president or vice president of a secret society that holds a grudge against humanity.

Born under an unfortunate fate, often defeated in the final episode or betrayed by an ally and lost.

Contrary to their attire, they are not prodigal or hedonistic, but rather a workaholic.

When their subordinates are about to lose, they administer a magic potion that makes them gigantic.

Considering compliance and adverse effects on the body, they try to entrust the initiative in battle to their subordinates as much as possible.

If they are commanders-in-chief, they may become so popular that a spin-off will be created.

They may overthrow heroes who have judicial, legislative, and executive powers.

items.name: Frankenstein
items.description:
Shout out to all the creators who did the hard work and made the models that I merged with. They are the real heros. Please support them :)

Fantastic Mix -- majicMIX realistic -- Cyber Realistic -- ICBINP -- Realistic Vision -- Fentexi_v0.9Beta

I've been using this merge for a little with decent results. People have been asking for it in the comments so Ima just throw it on here. It fits what I like to generate, and is not perfect, but I like the level of detail, realism, lighting, and how it reacts to my prompting.

I usually use it with DPM++ 2M Karras, but I've tested it on some other samplers with good results.

Clip skip 1 or 2 (I use 2). CFG 4-8 is the range I've tested in with good results.

Merge Process: Made a merge using my favorite realistic models. Focused on facial features, and consistency. I then used a combination (mainly majicMIX realistic), and Fentexi only on the input layer. Then, I threw my new custom realistic model on the output layer. A little bit of tweaking had to be done to get something I liked, but that was the general process.

Shout out to the Automatic1111 Super Merger extension. If you want to play around with merging it is a must add. I highly suggest learning about block merging, the input and output blocks and how they affect the output image. This article is a fantastic resource and taught me 90% of what I know. The SuperMerger Github README files are also very informative.

For this merge, I liked the composition of MajicMix realistic (poses, framing, higher level features, etc.), so, I threw mainly MajicMix on the input layer. The output layer will affect the art style, facial features, color (I think lol), etc. so I threw my custom realistic model on to the output. I am no expert, but this is how I understand the layers to work. Please correct me in the comments :)

I have tagged this as a NSFW model, as that is how I generally use it. It may produce good SFW results with the right prompting.

V2 because I didn't think V1 was worth posting. I don't expect to release any other versions, feel free to try and make it better because I'm lazy and I want ya'll to do the work for me :)

Sample images use all those negative textual inversions, I have had fine results using the model with and without them, use what you like best.

Happy Prompting!
